                    <abstract lang="eng">We consider the class of proper monotonic simple games and study coalition formation when an exogenous share vector and a solution concept are combined to guide the distribution of coalitional worth. Using a multiplicative composite solution, we induce players&apos; preferences over coalitions in a hedonic game, and present conditions under which the semistrict core of the game is nonempty.</abstract>
